---
By: Plutarch
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 20
    Verse: 15
Tags:
  - Anger
---
For he who gives no fuel to fire puts it out, and likewise he who does not
in the beginning nurse his wrath and does not puff himself up with anger
takes precautions against it and destroys it.
